AU  - Wahal, Sunil
T1  - Investing in a Global World*
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rft015
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 18
IS  - 2
SP  - 561
EP  - 590
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We examine active retail mutual funds and institutional products with a mandate to invest in global equity markets. We find little reliable evidence of alphas in the aggregate or on average. The right tail of the distribution contains some large alphas. Decomposing stock selection from country selection, we find some evidence of superior stock picking abilities in the extreme right tail. However, simulations suggest that they are produced just as likely by luck as by skill. Persistence tests show little evidence of continuation in superior performance.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rft015
ER  - 



